# <%= current_page.data.title %>

The intended readership of this page is new joiners to the team and the hiring Manager, the page illustrates Checklist to follow smooth Onboarding.

#### Step - 1 (Line Manager)

Request following items:

- Developer laptop

- User account(@justice.gov.uk)

- Gmail account(@digital.justice.gov.uk)

#### Step - 2 (Line Manager)

- Send instructions on how to obtain password from support desk via personal email before the start date.

- Arrange a call to kick-off onboarding process with the new joiner on the start date

#### Step - 3 (New joiner)

- Install tools as detailed [here](https://ministryofjustice.github.io/nvvs-devops/documentation/team-guide/team-tools.html#team-tools)

#### Step - 4 (New joiner)

- Follow README on this [repo](https://github.com/ministryofjustice/provision-ubuntu2004-on-wsl2)

#### Step - 5 (New joiner)

- Install Docker Desktop from [here](https://www.docker.com/products/docker-desktop/). Allow docker to be run by the authenticated user on your machine(run>compmgmt>local Users and Groups>docker-users>add authenticated users)
- Configure AWS Vault as detailed [here](https://ministryofjustice.github.io/nvvs-devops/documentation/team-guide/best-practices/use-aws-sso.html)

#### Step - 6 (New joiner)

Request access to the following :

- Github

- Jira

- IntelliJ IDEA

- NACs Admin

- DNS DHCP Admin

- Sentry.io

- Slack Channel

- Service Now

- Confluence

- PasswordManager (1Password) with access to the `Common Technology Services` vault.

- Account Associations:

    - User account(@justice.gov.uk): Associate with the group email<br/>
        `cloud-operations-notifications@justice.gov.uk`<br/>.

    - Gmail account(@digital.justice.gov.uk): Associate with the group email<br/>
        `lanwifi-devops@digital.justice.gov.uk`<br/>.

    - Github: Add Github account to the `nvvs-devops-admins` GitHub Team [here](https://github.com/ministryofjustice/staff-technology-services-github-teams)
